
                                            Banyana Banyan forward Thembi Kgatlana has been nominated for Women’s Player of the Year.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Banyana Banyana has been nominated for CAF’s Women’s National Team of the Year, with forward Thembi Kgatlana nominated for Women’s Player of the Year.  Dennis Onyango and Jeremy Brockie have been included in the list of Best African Player based in Africa. While African Player of the Year nominees include: Mohamed Salah, Pierre Emerick Aubamayang, Sadio Mane, Victor Moses and Bertrand Traore. And South African Luther Singh, who plays for Portuguese side Braga, is nominated for Youth Player of the Year.   